# <type>(<scope>): <imperative subject — max 72 chars>
#
# WHY this change exists. Not what — the diff shows that.
# Reference ADR, issue, or design doc if relevant.
#
# ─── AI DISCLOSURE ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# If AI (any tier) touched the code, add the line below and fill it in.
# Remove this block entirely if purely human-authored.
#
# Assisted-by: pi/tier<N>:<MODEL_ID> [clang-tidy] [scan-build]
# Example: Assisted-by: pi/tier2:Qwen/Qwen2.5-Coder-32B-Instruct [clang-tidy]
#
# Rules:
#   - Use the model ID from AGENTS.md § 14 (current weekly rotation)
#   - List only tools that materially shaped this commit
#   - Do NOT list: git, make, editors, ninja, cmake
#   - Multiple tiers = one Assisted-by line per tier
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Signed-off-by: Your Name <your@email.com>
#
# ─── TYPES ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# feat      new feature or behavior
# fix       bug fix
# refactor  structural change, no behavior change
# chore     build, toolchain, deps, config
# docs      documentation only
# test      test-only changes
# perf      performance improvement
#
# ─── SCOPES ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# <module-name>   e.g., parser, allocator, simd
# build           CMakeLists.txt, CMakePresets, cmake/
# ci              .github/workflows/
# docs            docs/, Doxyfile
# tests           tests/
# asm             Assembly-specific changes
# agents          AGENTS.md, .clang-format, .clang-tidy
